    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-05-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="185"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 579.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> You will learn by the journals that General
                    Hooker has crossed the Rappahannock and taken a position at Chancellorsville,
                    beyond the enemy at Fredericksburg. As the importance of this movement is
                    apparent, there has been intense anxiety here for the development of its
                    anticipated results. I had hoped to be able to give you some light upon the
                    subject in this despatch. General Hooker, however, keeps his counsels closely,
                    and, as we must suppose, wisely.</p>
                <p>I hardly need refer you to the gratifying intelligence which comes from Louisiana
                    and the Mississippi. The campaign in those regions seems to be advancing
                    prosperously.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
